ce:section.ce:para:
The optical properties of the CQDs and CQDs-N were investigated by UV−vis and photoluminescence (PL) spectroscopy. In the UV-vis spectra (Fig. 3
                        ), CQDs-N showed two characteristic peaks at 211 nm and 294 nm which has been attributed to various π−π* (C=C) and n−π* (C=O) transitions, while CQDs showed a strong UV-vis absorption feature centered at 230 nm. Under a hand-held UV lamp, CQDs-N produced blue light, and CQDs showed green light. In the PL spectrum (Fig. 4
                        ), there was an photoluminescent behavior both for CQDs and CQDs-N, which is similar to that reported for common CQDs [39,40].
